"   <div id=\"basicsTopicLeft\">",
"    <div id=\"topicTitle\">",
"     Patient information: Enterocutaneous fistula (The Basics)",
"    </div>",
"    <span class=\"view\">",
"     View in",
"     <a class=\"lang\" href=\"./es-419/enterocutaneous-fistula-the-basics?source=topic_page\">",
"      Spanish",
"     </a>",
"    </span>",
"    <a class=\"contributor contributor_credentials\" href=\"./authors-and-editors/patient-information\">",
"     Written by the doctors and editors at UpToDate",
"    </a>",
"    <div id=\"topicText\">",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H19859552\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What is an enterocutaneous fistula?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;An enterocutaneous fistula is an abnormal connection from the intestine to the skin (",
"      <a class=\"graphic graphic_figure graphicRef66110 \" href=\"UTD.htm?28/27/29107\">",
"       figure 1",
"      </a>",
"      ). It is a serious condition that might need to be treated in the hospital.",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H19859567\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       What are the symptoms of enterocutaneous fistula?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;The symptoms can include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bulletCompact-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Leakage of the intestines through an opening on the skin",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        A swollen, tender belly",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Fever",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        Diarrhea",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H19859582\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       Is there a test for enterocutaneous fistula?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;Yes. Your doctor or nurse should be able to tell if you have it by learning about your symptoms and doing an exam. But you might need tests that include:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bulletCompact-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        A CT scan &ndash; This is a special kind of X-ray.",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        A fistulogram &ndash; For this test, the doctor injects a dye into the opening of the skin of the fistula and then takes an X-ray.",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p class=\"headingAnchor\" id=\"H19859597\">",
"      <span class=\"h1\">",
"       How is an enterocutaneous fistula treated?",
"      </span>",
"      &nbsp;&mdash;&nbsp;You will be treated with:",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      <ul class=\"bullet-block\">",
"       <li>",
"        Fluids and medicines that go into a vein through a tube called an &ldquo;IV&rdquo; &nbsp;",
"       </li>",
"       <li>",
"        A tube (called a &ldquo;catheter&rdquo;) to help drain the fistula",
"       </li>",
"      </ul>",
"     </p>",
"     <p>",
"      Some people need surgery to repair the fistula.",
"     </p>",
"    </div>",
